HOLMES v WAYNE COUNTY CLERK Submitted January 25, 1974. (No. 20

January Term 1974,

Docket No. 55,545.) Decided January 28, 1974. Robert D. Randall (Douglas Elliart, of counsel), for plaintiff. J. W. Fitzgerald, J.

This case is governed by Vaughn v Wayne County Clerk, 391 Mich 1; 214 NW2d 320 (1974), this day released.

Writ of mandamus shall issue as prayed and the Clerk of this Court is directed to issue final process pursuant to GCR 1963, 866 forthwith.

No costs, a public question.

T. G. Kavanagh, Swainson, Williams, and Levin, JJ., concurred with J. W. Fitzgerald, J. *5T. M. Kavanagh, C. J., concurred in the result only. M. S. Coleman, J., did not sit in this case.
